00:33:29.040 --> 00:33:31.970
&gt;&gt; One of my friends on the
Internet has described Florida

00:33:31.970 --> 00:33:34.900
as being the only place
where you have to drive

00:33:34.900 --> 00:33:37.510
to north to get to the south.

00:33:37.510 --> 00:33:40.900
I'm wondering if you'd
care to elaborate on that.

00:33:40.900 --> 00:33:42.200
&gt;&gt; Carl Hiaasen: It's true.

00:33:42.200 --> 00:33:43.990
I mean, Florida -- people have
often said it could be three

00:33:43.990 --> 00:33:45.290
separate states.

00:33:45.290 --> 00:33:47.770
South Florida would be,
because of the Caribbean

00:33:47.770 --> 00:33:51.020
and South American
influence, would be one state.

00:33:51.020 --> 00:33:53.820
The central part, because
of Orlando and Disney

00:33:53.820 --> 00:33:55.150
and sort of the I-4 corridor.

00:33:55.150 --> 00:33:58.260
And then the panhandle, which
is really just southern Alabama

00:33:58.260 --> 00:34:00.980
and Mississippi and Georgia.

00:34:00.980 --> 00:34:04.460
And it's very three
distinct demographics.

00:34:04.460 --> 00:34:06.440
If you know, if you're going

00:34:06.440 --> 00:34:11.540
to hold a Donald Trump rally
would be much more well attended

00:34:11.540 --> 00:34:15.490
in Pensacola than it would be, for
instance, in Key West, Florida.

00:34:15.490 --> 00:34:20.530
Or at least it would be a more
tranquil event in Pensacola.

00:34:20.530 --> 00:34:23.780
Yes, it's a very interesting place
to be a journalist and a novelist

00:34:23.780 --> 00:34:25.200
because it's so different,
so diverse.

00:34:25.200 --> 00:34:26.760 position:56%
We have 20 million people there now.

00:34:26.760 --> 00:34:29.300 position:56%
We surpassed New York in population.

00:34:29.300 --> 00:34:33.080
Now, about half of those
people came from New York.

00:34:33.080 --> 00:34:36.820
But, and our governor's
very proud of how crowded

00:34:36.820 --> 00:34:39.710
and congested we are right now.

00:34:39.710 --> 00:34:42.070
He wants us to be number one.

00:34:42.070 --> 00:34:45.330
So, anyway.

00:34:45.330 --> 00:34:49.460
Yeah. I mean, it's just
-- it's just a great --

00:34:49.460 --> 00:34:51.740
I mean, it's a great
trove if you're a writer.

00:34:51.740 --> 00:34:56.470 position:56%
It's such an incredibly different --
you can in two hours literally feel

00:34:56.470 --> 00:35:00.350
like you've, you know, you're in
a whole other part of the world.

00:35:00.350 --> 00:35:02.350
And you might well be.

00:35:02.350 --> 00:35:03.650
Yes. Thanks.

